# World Operations

World operations cover two areas: **repo sync** (routine, use freely) and **service lifecycle** (usually operator territory).

## When to Sync

Sync fetches upstream changes into the managed repo. You need this when:

- **Before starting work that depends on latest main** — your worktree branches from the managed repo. If it's stale, your branch will be stale.
- **When merge conflicts appear** — an outdated base is the most common cause. Sync, then rebase your branch.
- **After a caravan phase completes** — the merged output from phase N should be in the managed repo before phase N+1 branches from it.

You do **not** need to sync before every action. Sync when staleness is causing problems or when you're about to start work that needs recent changes.

## Service Lifecycle

Service commands manage sphere daemons (prefect, sentinel, forge, consul, etc.). These are **usually operator territory** — use them only when:

- The operator explicitly asks you to install, uninstall, or stop services
- You're doing explicit infrastructure work that requires service restarts
- A service is clearly broken and needs to be cycled (and you've confirmed with the operator)

**`sol down`:** Stops all sphere daemons (prefect, consul, ledger, broker, chronicle) and world services (sentinel, forge) across **all worlds** — not just the current one. Use `sol down --world=<world>` to stop only a single world's services. `sol down --all` additionally kills envoy sessions sphere-wide — this is a much bigger hammer and should only be used when the operator requests a full shutdown.

## Failure Modes

- **Sync fails with conflict:** The managed repo has diverged in a way that can't be auto-resolved. Check `{{.Sol}} world status {{.World}}` and escalate if operator intervention is needed.
- **Service won't start:** Check logs and status. If the problem persists, escalate — don't repeatedly restart services hoping it fixes itself.

## Command Reference

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `{{.Sol}} world sync {{.World}}` | Sync managed repo from upstream |
| `{{.Sol}} world status {{.World}}` | World health overview |

### Service Lifecycle

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `{{.Sol}} service status` | Show all sphere daemon status |
| `{{.Sol}} service install` | Install systemd units |
| `{{.Sol}} service uninstall` | Remove systemd units |
| `{{.Sol}} down` | Stop all sphere daemons and world services across all worlds |
| `{{.Sol}} down --world=<world>` | Stop services for a single world only |
| `{{.Sol}} down --all` | Stop all services **and** kill envoy sessions sphere-wide |
